      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In the definition of a torus as a surface of revolution, the ring radius is the distance from the center of a circle (defined by the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scntorus/1522623-piperadius"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property) to the axis of revolution (the y-axis of the torus’s local coordinate space). Rotating the circle around the axis forms a pipe that follows a ring-shaped path."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The default ring radius is "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0.5"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". A ring radius of zero or less creates an empty geometry."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can animate changes to this property’s value. See "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/animation/animating_scenekit_content"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
